    "title": "Mid-Level Radiologist at Biocon Digital Technologies",
    "description": "Biocon Digital Technologies has an exciting opening for a Radiologist at our Thane office. Join a company that values innovation, collaboration, and continuous learning.\n\nAbout Biocon Digital Technologies:\nBiocon Digital Technologies is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Educate patients and families on health management and disease prevention\n• Administer medications and treatments as prescribed\n• Coordinate with multidisciplinary teams for comprehensive patient management\n• Adhere to NABH/JCI accreditation standards\n• Maintain sterile environments and follow infection control protocols\n• Participate in quality improvement initiatives and clinical audits\n• Attend continuing medical education programs and training\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Diploma or Degree in Hospitality Management\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Pharmacovigilance\n• Proficiency in Wound Care\n• Proficiency in Telemedicine\n• Proficiency in Medical Coding\n• Proficiency in Diagnostic Skills\n• Proficiency in Clinical Research\n• Proficiency in EMR/EHR\n• Proficiency in ICD-10\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Annual performance appraisal\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Flexible working hours\n• Modern office with recreational facilities\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Thane, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Biocon Digital Technologies!",
